---

### `app.js` — Line 18–19: Hardcoded port `3000`

The port number is hardcoded in two places:
```js
app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```

**Suggested fix:**
```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

